The Society for the Protection of our Constitution has described the parcel bomb incident in Durban as an act of terror. JOHANNESBURG - The Society for the Protection of our Constitution has described the parcel bomb incident in Durban as an act of terror.Three members of the Khan family have been left with serious injuries after a package that was delivered to their home exploded on Friday.The society s lawyer Zehir Omar says all three remain in hospital.Omar has called on state security to conduct forensic investigations to apprehend the culprits. The way the parcels were sent... the extent of the explosion and the injuries... the modus operandi clearly satisfies the mission of terrorism. This explosion was intended for the recipient to die. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)